    {
      "pos": [
        4478,
        4645
      ],
      "content": "Referring to Figure 1, let's look at some of the key parts of the Machine Learning Studio environment for working with the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Execute R Script<ept id=\"p1\">][execute-r-script]</ept> module."
    },
    {
      "content": "The modules in the experiment are shown in the center pane.",
      "pos": [
        4649,
        4708
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The upper part of the right pane contains a window to view and edit your R scripts.",
      "pos": [
        4712,
        4795
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The lower part of right pane shows some properties of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Execute R Script<ept id=\"p1\">][execute-r-script]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4801,
        4896
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can view the error and output logs by clicking on the appropriate spots of this pane.",
      "pos": [
        4897,
        4986
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4988,
        5110
      ],
      "content": "We will, of course, be discussing the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Execute R Script<ept id=\"p1\">][execute-r-script]</ept> in greater detail in the rest of this document."
    },
    {
      "content": "When working with complex R functions, I recommend that you edit, test and debug in RStudio.",
      "pos": [
        5112,
        5204
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "As with any software development, extend your code incrementally and test it on small simple test cases.",
      "pos": [
        5205,
        5309
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Then cut and paste your functions into the R script window of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Execute R Script<ept id=\"p1\">][execute-r-script]</ept> module.",
      "pos": [
        5310,
        5420
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This approach allows you to harness both the RStudio integrated development environment (IDE) and the power of Azure Machine Learning.",
      "pos": [
        5421,
        5555
      ]
    },
